This paper is about training neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the efficiency of mini-batch creation strategies, which is related to optimization and computational efficiency, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the experiments involve datasets with text and language, which could also fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
